1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,400
Let me introduce you to my brother.

2
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:09,360
His name's Koh.

3
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,600
If I had known we'd meet again,
I wouldn't have married Pun.

4
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,920
I don't know what to say.

5
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,360
This is how it is. What should I do?

6
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,920
Should I apologize and just leave?

7
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,040
But Pie does have good manners, Mom.

8
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:23,160
At least she doesn't badmouth others.

9
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,040
Has your wife brainwashed you
against your mother?

10
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,800
If Win accepts this job,

11
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,720
I'll step down.

12
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,640
Don't speak to me in that tone.

13
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:33,640
I don't like it.

14
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:37,080
Since we've known each other,
I've never asked you for anything before.

15
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,760
<i>This is the first time.</i>

16
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:40,400
Who do you care more about?

17
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:42,280
Your brother or your ex?

18
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,760
You have to choose.

19
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,080
Thank you.

20
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,920
Let's see what's on the table.

21
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,640
How's it going working with that girl?

22
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:07,160
Honestly, she's great!

23
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,120
I never thought Pie would have

24
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,280
such a vast knowledge
of fabrics in her head.

25
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,400
She's well-informed.

26
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,920
Whatever you ask her, she can answer.

27
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,240
If she doesn't know something,
she doesn't pretend to.

28
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:19,560
She just says,
"I'll find the information for you."

29
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,680
She's straightforward. I like that.

30
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,520
Hey, you've fallen into her trap.

31
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:30,240
That girl is a good actress.

32
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:33,840
She loves playing the innocent heroine,
making people fall for her.

33
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,880
Don't trust her.

34
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,920
Where are you going?

35
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,680
I'm going to pack
for my meditation retreat.

36
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:47,040
Again? Don't you think you go too often?

37
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,360
Are you trying to reach Nirvana?

38
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,840
Hey, Nhun.

39
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:52,120
Let him do good deeds.

40
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:55,720
He can do good at home.
We have plenty of space.

41
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,240
He can meditate anywhere
for peace and quiet.

42
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:00,360
There's no need to go
to a distant forest temple.

43
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,800
Well, it's peaceful and quiet out there.

44
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:06,640
And it's free from bad influences.

45
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,720
I'm off.

46
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,120
How boring.

47
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,400
Hey, Sil!

48
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:13,120
Are you calling me a bad influence?

49
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,080
Let's talk about this clearly!

50
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:17,040
Come on now.

51
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,880
We're getting older.

52
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:23,360
If your husband wants to take
the spiritual path, let him.

53
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:25,360
We're still full of desires.

54
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,000
Let's talk about the worldly things.

55
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,200
Nhun.

56
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,160
What do you think?

57
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:33,600
Is this a must-have? Look.

58
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,760
- No.
- What?

59
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:44,120
Welcome. You're Mr. Win, right?

60
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,680
Yes, I'm Win.

61
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:48,520
- You must be Ms. Mungmink.
- Yes.

62
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,040
Got any ideas after seeing the house?

63
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,320
The house has a lot of charm.

64
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:58,160
But as for ideas,
I'll need to go inside first.

65
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,400
Feel free to look around.

66
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,680
Let's take a look inside.

67
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:10,360
Good work, and he's hot in person too.

68
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,480
He's mine! I've already reserved him.

69
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,280
Does he know you've reserved him?

70
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,080
He doesn't know, but you should.

71
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,160
Don't steal from your friend.

72
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,520
From what I've seen of the house,

73
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,520
I think the house is already classic.
I don't want to change much.

74
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:46,440
I just want to improve it,
make the house more striking

75
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:47,480
and beautiful than before.

76
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:50,240
For example,
the lightwell in the center of the house.

77
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:54,600
I want to make it bigger
to let more light in.

78
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,920
Did you do your homework?

79
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,840
Of course, I did.

80
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,040
It seems you didn't do it well.

81
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,480
Pun, you said he was good.

82
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:19,440
So, why doesn't he know that natural light

83
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:22,440
is harmful to antiques,
especially the client's fabrics?

84
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:29,760
I didn't say I'd let the sunlight
shine directly on the fabrics.

85
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:33,760
What does the light hit then,
if not the fabric? The floor?

86
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,240
Of course, it'll hit the floor.

87
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,880
How do you know the fabric won't go there?

88
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:39,200
How do you know the fabrics
will be placed there?

89
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,200
I'm the one who arranges
where the fabric goes.

90
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:44,080
And I'm the one designing
where the fabric goes.

91
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,440
Enough!

92
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,760
We're on the same team.

93
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,640
Sort things out first, then present again.

94
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,480
I want the work done.

95
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,520
Not to hear you two argue.

96
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,000
Sorry.

97
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,640
In the meeting earlier,
were you trying to win against me?

98
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,800
You were throwing a tantrum,
getting upset,

99
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:46,600
thinking I'd give up
and let you quit, right?

100
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:50,680
Pun, I wouldn't use
childish tactics like that.

101
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,920
But what I said in the meeting
was the truth.

102
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:57,120
I wasn't throwing a tantrum,
but he was getting on my nerves.

103
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,160
You saw how he was arguing.

104
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,760
- Why blame me and not him?
- Okay, Pie.

105
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,120
Take it easy.

106
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:32,039
Well, let's talk this through.

107
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,799
I'm not blaming you, Pie.

108
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:39,320
I just want you to know
that what you showed earlier…

109
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,400
It wasn't sweet.

110
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,080
Exactly.

111
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,800
You're not just any employee.

112
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:48,480
You're my wife.

113
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:52,400
You're the face of me,
the face of the company.

114
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,080
Alright.

115
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,000
If you say you didn't do it
out of emotion,

116
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:04,640
that you weren't throwing a tantrum
to beat me, then we're done.

117
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:08,040
We won't bring this up again.

118
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,640
Is that alright?

119
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,960
That's really sweet.

120
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:25,960
See? When you're calm,
you're back to the Pie everyone loves.

121
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:36,600
Okay, the work issue is settled.

122
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:40,280
Now, let's talk
about something good for us.

123
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:45,760
Pie.

124
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:52,240
Do you remember
when I told you I spoke to Bee,

125
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:54,640
my friend who's a fertility doctor?

126
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,320
We've got an appointment now.

127
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,800
It's next Monday, the first slot.

128
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,960
Dr. Bee, my friend, is really skilled.

129
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:06,000
She specializes in this.

130
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:09,360
She told me, after the first consultation,

131
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:11,640
we'll do a health checkup
and start right away.

132
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,480
Yes.

133
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:19,840
It's this Monday, right?

134
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,000
That's right.

135
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:27,800
I'm taking the day off
to dedicate it to you.

136
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:31,400
So you don't have to stress.

137
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:34,440
Consider this the last project.

138
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:38,320
Once the job is done and the baby comes,

139
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,920
I won't have you working anymore.

140
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,640
I'll let you be a full-time mom
from then on.

141
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,880
How does that sound?

142
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:45,720
Okay?

143
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,600
IN VITRO FERTILIZATION
THE HOPE FOR THOSE WITH INFERTILITY

144
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,240
THREATENED MISCARRIAGE, A SERIOUS ISSUE
THAT CAN BE TREATED ON TIME

145
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:19,200
Two years of trying naturally
and still no children.

146
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:22,400
Medically, we consider this infertility.

147
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:27,280
So, what should we do next?

148
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:31,520
First, we need to identify the cause
and figure out what's going on.

149
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:34,320
Do either of you have
any chronic health conditions?

150
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,400
- No.
- No.

151
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:40,120
Do either of you smoke or drink alcohol?

152
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,440
Well, I do drink occasionally,
but I don't smoke.

153
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:46,120
Same here.

154
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,600
Excuse me, but have you

155
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:53,040
ever been pregnant
or had a miscarriage before?

156
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:58,320
Pie, answer the doctor.

157
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:04,120
Pie! Go ahead and answer!

158
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:06,840
Pie!

159
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,400
What? Going to the doctor on Monday?

160
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,600
Does the doctor
need to ask about a miscarriage?

161
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:40,320
I looked it up, and they do, Mom.

162
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:46,920
Then, when you talk to the doctor,
can Pun wait somewhere else?

163
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,840
Pun would want to be with me
every step of the way.

164
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:51,680
He took the day off
to join me at the doctor.

165
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,640
What should we do?

166
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,360
Mom.

167
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:05,000
I've made up my mind.

168
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,640
I'll tell Pun about my miscarriage.

169
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,640
Are you crazy?!

170
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,840
Why would you tell him?

171
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:11,320
It's the truth, Mom.

172
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,480
The longer I hide it, the guiltier I feel.

173
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:16,040
You're trying to make
yourself feel better,

174
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:19,120
but have you thought about how I'll be?

175
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,960
Pie, everything I have today,

176
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:26,320
everything I can afford,
is because of Pun.

177
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:30,720
What if you tell him,
and he wants the truth, then finds out

178
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,480
you were pregnant
before finishing university?

179
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:35,480
What will you do if he gets upset
and asks for a divorce?

180
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:38,080
No way, Pie!

181
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:41,040
You don't have a job,
and your savings aren't much.

182
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:44,600
Are you going to make me
go back to struggling again?

183
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:46,040
I can't do that!

184
00:13:53,680 --> 00:13:54,720
Pie.

185
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:59,680
I know you're hurting
for having to tell Pun the truth.

186
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:03,960
But telling the truth
might make everything worse.

187
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:06,920
Mom, if the doctor knows and tells Pun,
wouldn't that be just as bad?

188
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:14,840
Here's what we'll do.

189
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:17,760
You'll have to cancel Pun's doctor,

190
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,760
and I'll find a new one we can trust.

191
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:24,280
I'll also ask them
not to mention the miscarriage.

192
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:30,440
Mom, I can't just cancel it.

193
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:33,000
Pun's been waiting for this doctor,
and they're friends.

194
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,520
He's really invested.

195
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,560
Once he gets an appointment, he's going.

196
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:38,440
It's not something we can cancel.

197
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,560
You see the doctor on Monday?

198
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:44,040
Yes.

199
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:46,280
I'll find a way for you to avoid this.

200
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:51,200
But the best option
is for you to get pregnant naturally.

201
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,600
If you get pregnant,
all the problems will be solved.

202
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:56,640
Mom, it's only a few days away.

203
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:58,360
It's impossible. It just won't happen.

204
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:01,680
Everything was about to get better.

205
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:04,400
This problem happened
because of that idiot Win.

206
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:06,280
If I could go back in time,

207
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:08,240
I wouldn't have let you
go to Mae Hong Son.

208
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:10,280
Mom, can you stop saying that?

209
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,800
It can't be fixed now.

210
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:14,160
I don't want to say something unpleasant.

211
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,360
But isn't it true?

212
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:18,120
All our problems now are because of Win.

213
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,520
Luckily, he's out of our lives.

214
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,800
If not, I'd have made sure he was gone.

215
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:46,080
Surprise!

216
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:51,440
Surprise for the singles! Here you go.

217
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:57,000
- Chef Pun came himself?
- Let's try it.

218
00:17:08,119 --> 00:17:09,160
Hey.

219
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,480
What are you hiding?

220
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,839
Is there something you're hiding?

221
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,160
No, nothing.

222
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,440
Well, actually, look.

223
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,160
I have some unpaid bills.

224
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,960
There are a few of them.

225
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,200
Want to pay one of them?

226
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,160
Pay them yourself. You're an adult now.

227
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,600
You're working.

228
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,440
Hey.

229
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,080
But if you're really struggling,

230
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,680
tell Rok to advance your payment.

231
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:43,880
I'll approve it.

232
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,440
You're the big spender, huh?

233
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:49,920
Thanks!

234
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:54,040
You brat, don't flatter me.

235
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:55,720
Let's make the food.

236
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:13,480
Hurry up. The pan's hot!

237
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,200
- Almost done.
- Come on.

238
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:22,680
Here you go, Chef.

239
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:45,560
It looks amazing!

240
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:48,600
Is there anything you're not good at?

241
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,200
I must be good at this.

242
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:52,080
I've practiced making several dishes.

243
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:54,200
One day, I plan to cook for the kids.

244
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:59,000
Is Pie pregnant already?

245
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:02,280
Not yet, but soon.

246
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:03,880
I've booked a doctor's appointment.

247
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,880
Some things need a doctor's help.

248
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:10,240
Hurry up and get a wife and kids,
so they can be friends.

249
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,120
Pun.

250
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,680
A guy like me?

251
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:16,360
It'll be a long time.

252
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:20,040
Why? Don't you want a family?

253
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,560
Hey.

254
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:31,480
Honestly, I've never asked you
about your love life.

255
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:36,840
I remember the last time you told me
you met someone up north.

256
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:39,720
It seemed to be going well,
but then you broke up.

257
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,760
Why? What happened?

258
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:44,280
Tell me.

259
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,080
Tell me.

260
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:49,240
- My story?
- Yeah.

261
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:00,480
Are you sure you want to hear it?

262
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:03,160
I've been waiting to hear it.

263
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,920
- What's wrong, Koh?
- Ow!

264
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,520
- My eyes sting.
- Hey, what happened?

265
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:18,040
It burns! A chili got in my eye! Look!

266
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,480
What?

267
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,520
Squirming like you're going blind!

268
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:24,040
It really burns!

269
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:25,800
Hold on!

270
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,240
Pun!

271
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:33,760
- I'm here.
- Hurry, I can't take it anymore!

272
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:34,720
Where's the water?

273
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,640
Are you trying to help or kill me?

274
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:41,680
- Hey, it's still red!
- What?

275
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:42,760
Is it?

276
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:50,360
- That's intense!
- Intense, huh?

277
00:20:57,640 --> 00:20:58,520
Is this what you want?

278
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,400
- Don't, Pun! It still hurts!
- Come here.

279
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:04,120
- No more dabbing. It hurts!
- Stay still.

280
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,280
- Stop, Pun!
- Is this what you want?

281
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:08,640
Please, Pun! It hurts!

282
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:11,840
Don't, Koh!

283
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:14,360
- Your turn!
- Stop, Koh!

284
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:17,760
<i>Why do Pie and Win</i>
<i>not get along this badly?</i>

285
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:20,000
Ever since Win started helping Pun,
Pie has changed.

286
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:23,400
The variable is Win,
who just came back to Pun.

287
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:25,320
That's what made Pie change.

288
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:28,320
Something must have happened
between the three of them.

289
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:33,600
Pun and Win must be having an affair.

290
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,440
Did you really see it, Mink?

291
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,640
With my own eyes!

292
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:41,000
I was going to give Win a book,

293
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:42,440
and then I froze.

294
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:43,440
I didn't dare go in.

295
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:46,160
The vibe wasn't brotherly at all.

296
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:47,520
It was definitely like a couple.

297
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:51,520
That's why Pie's not okay with Win.

298
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:54,360
I think Pun brought Pie in
to be a baby making machine.

299
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,200
But honestly, he doesn't like women.

300
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:58,600
He's gay, just married to cover it up.

301
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:04,240
Tell me. What do you know? Spill it now.

302
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:09,000
When I asked Pun why Pie doesn't like Win,

303
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:10,400
he answered…

304
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:13,520
I brought Win to stay at my place,
but I didn't tell Pie beforehand.

305
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,480
When she woke up and saw him,
she was shocked.

306
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:17,160
They've been fighting since they met.

307
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:20,640
Even now,
Pie's still being cold toward Win.

308
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:22,560
<i>She lashed out at him in the meeting room.</i>

309
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,680
Clearly.

310
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:25,280
I think Pie must've seen worse.

311
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:27,760
That's why she's in shock.

312
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:33,080
It might make sense if Pun thinks of Pie
as a baby making machine.

313
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,640
Because he really wants kids.

314
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:38,640
Every time I ask Pie
why she doesn't like Win,

315
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,600
she never answers.

316
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:43,040
Oh no, Pun.

317
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:46,840
Please, Pun can't be like that.

318
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,680
And if it's true,

319
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:51,240
what will Pie do next?

320
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:58,200
Pie!

321
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:59,600
I brought you some food.

322
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,480
Eat something tasty to avoid stress.

323
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:03,160
Mom, just put it on the table.

324
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,440
I'll eat it later. I'm in a hurry.

325
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:07,160
Hey, wait a minute.
It's only half an hour.

326
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:08,360
You'll be done soon.

327
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:10,720
I can't, Mom.
My car is in for maintenance.

328
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:11,920
Pun booked a van for me.

329
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,600
I need to be on time. I have to go now.

330
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:15,160
Oh, wait, Pie.

331
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:16,480
What's all that stuff? Is it heavy?

332
00:23:16,560 --> 00:23:18,960
Let me help, Pie.

333
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:21,200
Wait, is the van not available?

334
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:22,480
It's not available.

335
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:25,160
But Pun said he already booked it for me.

336
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:26,480
Yeah, that's what I thought.

337
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:29,760
Pun booked it.
Pie needs to use the van today.

338
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:31,360
- Well, actually--
- You can't use it.

339
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,200
Because I need it.
I have some errands to run.

340
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,080
Hello, Nhun.

341
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:41,400
Are you going out?

342
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:43,560
Would you like me to give you a ride?

343
00:23:43,640 --> 00:23:46,160
Pun booked the van for Pie,

344
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:49,200
so it will take her
to the office as planned.

345
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:51,520
It's fine. I'll go on my own.

346
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:52,880
Let Mom take the van instead.

347
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:54,480
That's how it should be.

348
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,280
You should learn
to go on your own sometimes.

349
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:59,800
The van is for picking me up.

350
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:04,360
I understand. Pun booked it
for me, and I didn't know.

351
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:05,720
I'm sorry.

352
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,760
Mom, let's go.

353
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:17,080
- Pie.
- Mom!

354
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:18,080
Nhun, actually,

355
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:20,400
- Mom!
- Pie is the daughter-in-law of this house,

356
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:22,520
and you can't blame her for this

357
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:25,040
- because Pun booked the van for her.
- Mom.

358
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:27,160
If you don't want her to use it,

359
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,880
you'll have to tell Pun yourself.

360
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:31,320
Oh, or actually,

361
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:35,040
do you want Pie to go tell him
to buy a new van?

362
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:38,640
- One that's just for Pie and Pun.
- Mom!

363
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,080
Hey!

364
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:43,800
Even though my family is wealthy,
I'm careful with money.

365
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:47,280
I'm not like some people who waste money
and end up with nothing.

366
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:50,400
All that's left is the outer shell,
and they still can't manage money.

367
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:54,120
If you're talking about me,

368
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:56,240
I know how to manage money.

369
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:58,320
If you don't believe me,
transfer some and I'll show you.

370
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:00,720
So this is how you beg.

371
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:03,240
How many millions have you
drained from my son already?

372
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:07,280
If your family is really rich,
this shouldn't be an issue.

373
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:08,800
It won't even affect you.

374
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:09,760
Mom!

375
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:11,480
Or maybe, in reality,

376
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,560
you're just all show,
like you've said about others.

377
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:15,320
Hey, that's too much!

378
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,120
- Mom!
- That's still too little.

379
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:18,480
- Let's go!
- You always do this!

380
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,120
- You talk down to others.
- Stop it, Mom!

381
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:22,160
- Mom!
- Let go!

382
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:24,760
- Tian, go get the driver now!
- Let go of me!

383
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:27,880
I'm going to buy coffee
at the corner. Quickly!

384
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:33,880
Why do we have to give in to her?

385
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:37,120
She's doing this on purpose
to show that we're unimportant.

386
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,720
Mom, just leave it.
I don't want to make a fuss.

387
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:44,200
It's because you're giving in
that she's able to push us down like this.

388
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:47,480
I'm telling you, we need
to stand up for ourselves.

389
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:49,800
And don't worry about the inheritance.

390
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,040
Since Pun is the only son,

391
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:55,160
the inheritance
will eventually go to your child.

392
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:57,640
Mom, I don't want it.

393
00:25:57,720 --> 00:25:59,120
But I want it.

394
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:05,160
Once I get it,
I'll save it for your chlid.

395
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:07,800
And you need to keep it for yourself too.

396
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:10,840
Pie, you're going to be a mother soon.

397
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:14,680
You can't just be good
and self-sacrificing about these things.

398
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,840
Don't you understand?

399
00:26:15,920 --> 00:26:19,920
You need to take his money
and save it for the future of your child.

400
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:25,760
But for now, give me the money.

401
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:27,040
We need to get on the expressway.

402
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:28,920
Here you go.

403
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:31,200
See, Pie?

404
00:26:31,280 --> 00:26:35,240
Nowadays, everywhere we go, we need money.

405
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:39,120
You can't avoid taking money
from his family. Got it?

406
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:56,600
Thank you, Mom.

407
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,600
Are you okay, Pie?

408
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:06,640
I'm fine.

409
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:10,200
- Do you want me to help?
- It's fine, Mom.

410
00:27:10,280 --> 00:27:12,400
I can carry it myself.
You should hurry up and go.

411
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,480
Thank you.

412
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:37,760
NATURE OF LIFE

413
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:40,480
- No need to help.
- If you don't want to be near me,

414
00:27:40,560 --> 00:27:41,680
just head into the office.

415
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,160
I'll pick up the books for you.

416
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:10,040
Pie!

417
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:12,960
You refuse to take money
from your mother-in-law

418
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:15,000
and forgot your own money as well.

419
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:46,400
That jerk, Win!

420
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:52,120
What is he doing at Pun's office?

421
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:03,400
This is bad.

422
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:07,880
Pie, didn't you take the van?

423
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:09,640
I already booked it for you.

424
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:13,320
Well, Mom needed the van for an errand.

425
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:16,280
Wait a minute.

426
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:19,640
The rule in our house is whoever
books it first gets to use it.

427
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:22,520
My mom has another van.
Why did she take this one?

428
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:23,720
I need to sort this out.

429
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,800
It's okay, Pun.

430
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:28,720
- I've here now.
- No, Pie.

431
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:31,520
I follow all of Mom's rules,
and when she does this,

432
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:33,080
it makes me look incompetent.

433
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:35,200
It's not that big of a deal, Pun

434
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,360
Pun.

435
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:41,360
Mom, I'm not okay with the van situation.

436
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:44,320
I booked it for Pie.

437
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:45,720
I follow all of your rules.

438
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:47,960
Why aren't you following your own rules?

439
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:49,800
Did your wife go and complain?

440
00:29:50,840 --> 00:29:53,040
She didn't complain.
She just told the truth.

441
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:56,080
Honestly, where did you take the van, Mom?

442
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:59,320
Why? Can't I use the van?

443
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:01,200
Does your wife think she's too important?

444
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:04,000
It's not about that, Mom.

445
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:07,680
You can use the van
whenever you want, but I reserved it.

446
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:10,960
I've never booked one for her before,
and you know that.

447
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:13,720
When you do this,

448
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:17,200
it makes me look like
I can't lead our family properly.

449
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,360
<i>Hold on, Pun.</i>

450
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:24,240
<i>What did she say</i>
<i>to make you misunderstand like this?</i>

451
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:25,920
<i>This is all nonsense.</i>

452
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,400
She must have slandered me.

453
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:29,240
That's why you're so upset with me.

454
00:30:29,320 --> 00:30:30,440
Mom.

455
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,800
She didn't slander you at all.

456
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:34,440
She didn't say anything bad.

457
00:30:35,560 --> 00:30:37,240
Okay, Mom, let's end this.

458
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:40,680
I hope this will be
the last time this happens.

459
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:43,160
I've followed all of your rules.

460
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:44,840
I just want you to respect me as well.

461
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:49,320
I also have to take care of Pie
as my wife.

462
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:53,520
Please cooperate, Mom.

463
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:01,920
Dream on about me cooperating.

464
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:06,640
With that sweet face,
look at how sneaky she is.

465
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:14,640
Pie.

466
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:18,040
I've handled it.

467
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:20,320
This won't happen again.

468
00:31:21,320 --> 00:31:22,200
Okay?

469
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:24,840
Okay.

470
00:31:27,680 --> 00:31:29,120
Alright, let's get to work.

471
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:37,000
<i>Why is Win at Pun's office?</i>

472
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:50,800
- Thank you.
- Pie.

473
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,320
Are you okay?

474
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:56,160
Still upset about earlier?

475
00:31:56,880 --> 00:31:58,480
No, I'm fine now. It's just…

476
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:02,080
My hand's a little numb,
but it's nothing serious.

477
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:04,040
- You okay?
- Yes.

478
00:32:04,120 --> 00:32:06,240
Alright, let's get to work. Hey, sit down.

479
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:18,000
Excuse me.

480
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,920
- Come in, Rok.
- Pie.

481
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,320
Your mom asked me to bring this.

482
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:22,840
You left it in the car.

483
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:27,520
She asked you to come by after work
to discuss something.

484
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:31,520
Bye.

485
00:32:58,200 --> 00:33:01,080
If I didn't see Win myself and asked Rok,

486
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:02,280
would you have told me

487
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:05,400
that Win is Pun's neighbor
and working at the company?

488
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:08,360
How long are you going to keep lying to me
and hiding things?

489
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:11,400
Don't you remember how things went
last time when you lied to me?

490
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:12,840
Mom, can you please calm down?

491
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:13,720
I'm not calm.

492
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,880
Rok said you have to work with him too?

493
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:19,520
Mom, I didn't want to do it,
but Pun forced me.

494
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:21,000
Don't let him force you.

495
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,440
Just tell him you don't want to do it.

496
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:24,640
I've tried talking to him,
but it didn't work.

497
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,560
The only way is to tell him everything.

498
00:33:30,360 --> 00:33:33,640
Tell him exactly what happened
between Win and me.

499
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:37,440
Then he'll understand
why we can't work together.

500
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:42,200
Mom, Pun and I are fighting over work,
and our marriage is falling apart.

501
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:44,960
I don't want to stay in something toxic.

502
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:51,480
Alright, Pie.

503
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:54,320
But first,

504
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:58,360
you can't fight with Pun
because he doesn't know about this.

505
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:01,280
Mom, I understand.

506
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:03,160
I understand everything.

507
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:06,120
And I knew that if you found out,
you'd react like this.

508
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:09,280
That's why I didn't want to tell you
because we'd just argue like this.

509
00:34:11,920 --> 00:34:14,719
If we lie about one thing,
then we'll have to keep lying.

510
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:16,560
That's why they say not to lie, Mom.

511
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:19,960
Yeah, I get it.

512
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:23,480
We just didn't tell the whole truth.

513
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:26,440
- So it's not really a lie.
- Hold on, Mom.

514
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:28,639
What's the difference?

515
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:32,560
Just think of it as having
a secret from your husband.

516
00:34:33,159 --> 00:34:34,440
But don't think of it as lying.

517
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,280
We just didn't tell him.

518
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:40,199
Well, Pun must keep
some secrets from you too.

519
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:44,960
Mom, it's up to you.

520
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:47,880
Whatever makes you feel comfortable,
just think that way.

521
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:53,199
Pie, you need to be careful too.

522
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:55,120
Don't give in to Win.

523
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:57,320
Don't worry, Mom.

524
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:59,080
I haven't forgotten what he did.

525
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:01,800
Good. I haven't forgotten either.

526
00:35:23,960 --> 00:35:25,720
Are you happy now?

527
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:38,160
Mom.

528
00:35:39,320 --> 00:35:41,320
Mom, about the van today…

529
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:42,960
You made mother and son fight.

530
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:44,920
Are you happy now?

531
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:48,280
Since Pun was born,

532
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:51,480
he has never acted like this
with me before.

533
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,040
I'm sorry. I didn't mean it.

534
00:35:55,120 --> 00:35:56,320
You didn't mean it,

535
00:35:56,400 --> 00:35:58,440
and yet he is still scolding me like this.

536
00:35:58,520 --> 00:36:01,480
If you meant it, I'd probably
be completely cut off as a mother.

537
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:04,240
By messing with him like this,

538
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:07,120
you're trying to compete
for importance with me?

539
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:09,920
No, Mom. I never thought like that.

540
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,760
You didn't think it, but you did it.

541
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:15,880
Sure, go ahead.

542
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:17,720
I want to know too.

543
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:21,480
If one day Pun has to choose
between you and me,

544
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:24,840
let's see who he'll choose.

545
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:22,640
Does your mom want more money?

546
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,320
You came back looking so serious.

547
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:30,240
If she does, just let me know.

548
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,360
I don't want you to be stressed.

549
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:36,720
It's not about the money, Pun.

550
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:45,280
If it's not about money,

551
00:37:47,640 --> 00:37:49,000
then what is it?

552
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:56,000
Just something trivial.

553
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:02,200
Something trivial?

554
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:05,320
Then why do you look so serious?

555
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:11,480
Is there something
you're not telling me, Pie?

556
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:15,720
You know I don't like it
when you keep secrets from me.

557
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:25,440
It's not really a secret, Pun.

558
00:38:26,600 --> 00:38:27,640
It's just…

559
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:33,120
The argument with the neighbors.

560
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:36,840
She was complaining to me,
and I got stressed about it.

561
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:40,920
I didn't want to tell you
because you'd get stressed too.

562
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:42,440
That's all.

563
00:38:50,160 --> 00:38:53,440
If you don't want me to get stressed,

564
00:38:56,040 --> 00:38:57,360
you know…

565
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:01,120
what I like you to do, right?

566
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:09,440
We haven't had a chance
to unwind together in a while, Pie.

567
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:10,560
Pun.

568
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:22,640
Pun, I'll go take a shower first.

569
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:26,480
I'm tired.

570
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:40,200
It's because you're like this
that we still don't have any children.

571
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:15,400
Today, I'll go check the place again.

572
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:17,480
The measurements last time were too vague.

573
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:20,520
- Should I go with you?
- No need.

574
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:22,040
You stay here and work.

575
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,080
Finish up quickly.

576
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:26,120
This evening, I'll call you later.

577
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:29,080
And we'll…

578
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,240
get some arm exercises in.

579
00:41:36,080 --> 00:41:38,720
Sure. I'll stand by and wait.

580
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:42,560
Wow, now it's obvious.

581
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:46,560
But will your wife be okay
with you going with me?

582
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:48,440
Hey.

583
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:51,520
She'll be fine. She's okay with it.

584
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:55,360
See you this evening.

585
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,560
- Finish your work quickly.
- Okay.

586
00:42:06,200 --> 00:42:07,400
Oh my.

587
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:31,080
Pun!

588
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,120
Mink!

589
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:35,800
Hold on, Mink!

590
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:37,600
Let me see.

591
00:42:44,920 --> 00:42:45,760
You're bleeding.

592
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:04,240
Hey, if helping me ends up hurting you,

593
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:06,840
don't help next time.

594
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:12,480
This is the most painful thank you
I've ever heard.

595
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:15,560
Well, it's true.

596
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:19,200
If you didn't help me,
you wouldn't have gotten hurt.

597
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:22,040
Maybe

598
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:24,480
I have a harder head than you.

599
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:26,400
Alright.

600
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:29,000
Okay.

601
00:43:29,520 --> 00:43:31,480
Sorry for helping.

602
00:43:33,480 --> 00:43:34,520
Everything I do feels wrong.

603
00:43:38,960 --> 00:43:39,960
I was just kidding.

604
00:43:44,560 --> 00:43:45,880
Really, I was just kidding.

605
00:43:47,520 --> 00:43:49,000
Thanks for helping me.

606
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:19,560
Why aren't you eating?

607
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:24,040
I don't like vegetables.

608
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:27,040
Then why didn't you order it
without vegetables?

609
00:44:27,120 --> 00:44:29,680
I forgot. I was distracted
by other things.

610
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:32,320
I don't like it.
I don't want to eat anymore.

611
00:44:35,800 --> 00:44:36,880
If you're not eating, can I have it?

612
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:43,360
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

613
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:46,520
One red pork noodles, no vegetables,
and dumplings.

614
00:44:46,600 --> 00:44:47,600
Got it.

615
00:44:48,960 --> 00:44:50,400
Don't worry.
This bowl's without vegetables.

616
00:44:51,080 --> 00:44:51,920
Is that okay?

617
00:44:53,120 --> 00:44:54,040
Thanks.

618
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:55,320
It's no big deal.

619
00:44:55,400 --> 00:44:57,200
I was going to order two bowls anyway.

620
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:05,600
Win, can I ask you something?

621
00:45:06,120 --> 00:45:07,000
Yeah?

622
00:45:08,200 --> 00:45:09,320
Have you ever been in a relationship?

623
00:45:12,080 --> 00:45:13,920
At my age, of course.

624
00:45:15,520 --> 00:45:17,280
With that look, you're definitely popular.

625
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:19,040
How many relationships have you had?

626
00:45:23,640 --> 00:45:24,720
I don't remember.

627
00:45:37,360 --> 00:45:38,280
Were they women or men?

628
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:42,120
Drink some water.

629
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:45,240
Here, go ahead.

630
00:45:48,040 --> 00:45:49,320
Are you okay?

631
00:45:54,320 --> 00:45:56,480
Why are you asking me this?

632
00:45:56,560 --> 00:45:58,640
Me? Cheating on Pie?

633
00:45:59,640 --> 00:46:00,960
What makes you think that?

634
00:46:02,240 --> 00:46:04,320
Mink, tell me.

635
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:07,120
Why are you asking? What's going on?

636
00:46:09,800 --> 00:46:12,320
What exactly
is your relationship with Win?

637
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:13,840
Huh?

638
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:15,600
Me and who?

639
00:46:15,680 --> 00:46:17,120
Me and Pun?

640
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:20,760
Yes! You and Pun
are more than just brothers, right?

641
00:46:20,840 --> 00:46:23,840
No, we're not like that.

642
00:46:23,920 --> 00:46:25,280
Are you watching too many BL series?

643
00:46:25,360 --> 00:46:27,560
How did you come up with that idea?

644
00:46:28,080 --> 00:46:29,760
Win is really my younger brother.

645
00:46:30,360 --> 00:46:31,440
I'm asking seriously.

646
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:34,000
Where did you get the idea
that Win and I are something?

647
00:46:34,080 --> 00:46:37,520
Since you came into the picture,
Pie doesn't seem happy.

648
00:46:38,040 --> 00:46:39,720
And she seems distant from Pun.

649
00:46:40,320 --> 00:46:43,440
You seem closer to Win
and give him more attention than Pie.

650
00:46:43,520 --> 00:46:46,520
Pie looks upset,
not happy when she's with you.

651
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:50,320
So, I thought you married Pie
just to cover up.

652
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:52,600
You'd rush to have a child
to cover up the gay rumors.

653
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:55,040
No, you're overthinking it.

654
00:46:55,120 --> 00:46:58,240
I'm not gay, and Win isn't either.

655
00:46:58,760 --> 00:47:00,400
We are just brothers.

656
00:47:00,480 --> 00:47:03,600
Pun and I are not anything.

657
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:07,000
If you don't believe me,
I'll swear anywhere you want.

658
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,520
That's a relief.

659
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:11,760
I thought you might be the third wheel.

660
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:13,520
But I swear,

661
00:47:13,600 --> 00:47:17,440
I won't let anyone
come between Pun and Pie's family.

662
00:47:17,520 --> 00:47:20,280
I won't do that. Don't worry.

663
00:47:21,240 --> 00:47:22,400
Is that clear?

664
00:47:22,920 --> 00:47:26,120
There's nothing between me and Win
beyond being brothers, okay?

665
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:28,400
Okay, it's clear now.

666
00:47:28,480 --> 00:47:29,600
Are we clear on this?

667
00:47:29,680 --> 00:47:31,520
Totally clear!

668
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:38,120
But there's one thing
I haven't cleared up.

669
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:41,920
Do you really think Pie isn't happy
when she's with me?

670
00:47:45,680 --> 00:47:46,960
What do you think?

671
00:47:48,400 --> 00:47:50,440
I never thought Pie wouldn't be happy.

672
00:47:53,480 --> 00:47:55,000
Since you got married,

673
00:47:55,960 --> 00:47:57,560
have you been happy?

674
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:03,320
Of course.

675
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:05,520
I'm happy.

676
00:48:06,520 --> 00:48:08,640
Being with Pie has never been a problem

677
00:48:09,440 --> 00:48:11,080
because she's a good person.

678
00:48:11,160 --> 00:48:12,840
She's never made me feel uncomfortable.

679
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:18,600
Do you realize that you hesitated
before answering?

680
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:22,920
I don't know why you paused.

681
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:27,840
But maybe you should ask yourself again

682
00:48:28,360 --> 00:48:30,200
if you're really happy.

683
00:48:34,840 --> 00:48:36,600
Thank you for taking care of the wound.

684
00:49:18,640 --> 00:49:19,800
Ma'am.

685
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:22,640
No need for all the formalities.

686
00:49:24,200 --> 00:49:26,800
I have something to say,
and I'll be leaving soon.

687
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:42,760
You know, right?

688
00:49:42,840 --> 00:49:46,000
Pie is happy with Pun right now.

689
00:49:46,600 --> 00:49:48,360
If you still have any decency left,

690
00:49:48,440 --> 00:49:50,840
don't destroy her life
for the second time.

691
00:49:51,440 --> 00:49:53,280
I didn't come back to Thailand yesterday.

692
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:56,040
If Pun and Pie are still together today,

693
00:49:56,120 --> 00:49:58,680
it means I never thought
about ruining their lives.

694
00:49:58,760 --> 00:50:00,880
If I wanted to,
I would've done it already.

695
00:50:00,960 --> 00:50:02,600
Are you threatening me?

696
00:50:04,040 --> 00:50:05,080
Okay.

697
00:50:05,680 --> 00:50:07,560
I'll keep my words to a minimum

698
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:10,160
because no matter what I say,
you'll just see it negatively.

699
00:50:10,760 --> 00:50:13,360
If you have something to say,
go ahead. I'm listening.

700
00:50:13,440 --> 00:50:15,680
Not just listening,
but follow through as well.

701
00:50:17,840 --> 00:50:20,640
First, keep your distance from Pie
as much as possible.

702
00:50:21,360 --> 00:50:25,240
Second, don't talk
about the past to anyone.

703
00:50:25,320 --> 00:50:28,720
Not just with Pun, but with everyone.

704
00:50:28,800 --> 00:50:31,920
Third, don't cross the line.

705
00:50:32,600 --> 00:50:35,040
Right now, you're just a colleague.

706
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:38,440
Don't think of yourself as anything more.

707
00:50:39,040 --> 00:50:41,640
Honestly, just quit!

708
00:50:41,720 --> 00:50:43,800
The best thing to do
is stop working together.

709
00:50:43,880 --> 00:50:46,800
I've tried, but it hasn't worked.

710
00:50:47,560 --> 00:50:49,040
If you want me to quit,

711
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:52,200
you should talk to Pun, not me.

712
00:50:53,360 --> 00:50:55,040
That's just an excuse.

713
00:50:55,120 --> 00:50:58,000
If you really didn't want to do this,
who's stopping you?

714
00:50:58,520 --> 00:51:01,960
It seems like you don't
really know your son-in-law.

715
00:51:03,880 --> 00:51:07,160
Would you like me to call Pun
and tell him I'm quitting?

716
00:51:07,240 --> 00:51:08,840
Let's see what happens then.

717
00:51:09,760 --> 00:51:11,640
Hey!

718
00:51:11,720 --> 00:51:12,960
Are you crazy?

719
00:51:13,040 --> 00:51:15,200
If you call now, he will be suspicious.

720
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:16,600
Exactly.

721
00:51:16,680 --> 00:51:20,080
If I say I'm quitting,
he's going to ask why.

722
00:51:20,160 --> 00:51:23,080
And if I don't want to lie,
or if I can't pull it off,

723
00:51:23,160 --> 00:51:26,760
he will find out the truth
that you don't want him to know.

724
00:51:33,720 --> 00:51:35,640
Pie and I love Pun.

725
00:51:36,280 --> 00:51:39,440
And we know how to behave and what to do.

726
00:51:39,520 --> 00:51:43,600
We've been trying hard
to finish this project and separate.

727
00:51:43,680 --> 00:51:45,840
I know my place,

728
00:51:45,920 --> 00:51:48,040
and you should know yours too.

729
00:51:48,840 --> 00:51:51,400
Are you saying I'm meddling?

730
00:51:52,000 --> 00:51:54,080
Let's not talk about this any further.

731
00:51:54,160 --> 00:51:55,560
We'll just end up arguing.

732
00:51:55,640 --> 00:51:58,840
I understand what you want.

733
00:51:59,720 --> 00:52:01,480
I'll end the conversation here.

734
00:52:05,280 --> 00:52:06,560
You may leave.

735
00:52:27,600 --> 00:52:29,160
Why did you go talk to him, Mom?

736
00:52:30,080 --> 00:52:31,680
How did you know where he's staying?

737
00:52:33,280 --> 00:52:34,240
Krarok.

738
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:38,520
Mom, didn't she find it suspicious
that you asked where he is staying?

739
00:52:39,480 --> 00:52:42,320
I lied, saying that Win
is the son of a friend,

740
00:52:42,400 --> 00:52:44,320
and that I had a small gift to deliver.

741
00:52:45,440 --> 00:52:49,720
Mom, I'm starting to wonder
if you're a scammer.

742
00:52:49,800 --> 00:52:52,320
You can't keep lying like this, Mom!

743
00:52:52,400 --> 00:52:54,400
If the truth comes out one day,
what will you do?

744
00:52:55,000 --> 00:52:56,920
Pie, you're overreacting.

745
00:52:57,000 --> 00:52:59,400
I was just playing a little drama.

746
00:52:59,480 --> 00:53:01,000
Rok didn't seem to mind at all.

747
00:53:01,080 --> 00:53:02,760
You know your friend's personality well.

748
00:53:02,840 --> 00:53:07,080
Besides, she was really happy to hear
that Win is my friend's son.

749
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:08,840
She even said, "The world is so small!"

750
00:53:11,680 --> 00:53:12,680
Mom.

751
00:53:13,200 --> 00:53:16,280
I'm starting to lose it
with all the complications

752
00:53:16,360 --> 00:53:18,400
caused by these lies.

753
00:53:18,920 --> 00:53:20,760
If you don't stop causing trouble,

754
00:53:20,840 --> 00:53:23,560
I'll reveal the truth
and end all these problems.

755
00:53:23,640 --> 00:53:26,360
Pie, I'm not causing trouble.

756
00:53:26,440 --> 00:53:28,680
I'm just telling Win
not to create any more problems.

757
00:53:28,760 --> 00:53:31,240
But you're causing trouble
without realizing it.

758
00:53:33,200 --> 00:53:35,000
If you go see Win again,

759
00:53:35,720 --> 00:53:37,120
I won't stand for it.

760
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:41,360
Pie.

761
00:53:47,920 --> 00:53:49,840
I won't go see Win again.

762
00:53:50,920 --> 00:53:54,720
But if he bothers you again,
I won't let him get away with it.

763
00:53:58,480 --> 00:54:02,320
Pie.

764
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:04,760
Aren't you going to have dinner with me?

765
00:54:04,840 --> 00:54:06,880
I bought so much food.

766
00:54:06,960 --> 00:54:09,240
You're leaving me to eat alone again?

767
00:54:20,920 --> 00:54:23,080
All our problems now are because of Win.

768
00:54:23,160 --> 00:54:26,320
It's because you're like this
that we still don't have any children.

769
00:54:26,400 --> 00:54:27,680
<i>I'll tell Pun about my miscarriage.</i>

770
00:54:27,760 --> 00:54:29,400
<i>Are you crazy?!</i>

771
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:31,040
What will you do if he asks for a divorce?

772
00:54:31,120 --> 00:54:33,720
Have you thought about how I'll be?

773
00:54:33,800 --> 00:54:35,520
Dr. Bee, my friend, is really skilled.

774
00:54:35,600 --> 00:54:36,960
We've got an appointment now.

775
00:54:37,040 --> 00:54:38,240
It's next Monday, the first slot.

776
00:54:39,000 --> 00:54:40,480
<i>You had a miscarriage.</i>

777
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:41,960
No one will know about this.

778
00:54:42,040 --> 00:54:43,640
<i>And it never happened.</i>

779
00:54:45,400 --> 00:54:48,000
<i>If I had known we'd meet again,</i>
<i>I wouldn't have married Pun.</i>

780
00:54:49,120 --> 00:54:51,800
If one day Pun has to choose
between you and me,

781
00:54:51,880 --> 00:54:55,600
- let's <i>see who he'll choose.</i>
<i>- If you go see Win again,</i>

782
00:54:55,680 --> 00:54:56,960
I won't stand for it.

783
00:54:57,040 --> 00:54:59,040
If he bothers you again,

784
00:54:59,120 --> 00:55:00,560
<i>I won't let him get away with it.</i>

785
00:55:00,640 --> 00:55:03,440
I'm starting to lose it
with all the complications

786
00:55:03,520 --> 00:55:05,280
<i>caused by these lies.</i>

787
00:55:05,360 --> 00:55:07,120
<i>If you don't stop causing trouble,</i>

788
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:09,840
I'll reveal the truth
and end all these problems.

789
00:55:27,760 --> 00:55:31,720
How much longer do you think
you can endure this, Pie?

790
00:56:06,720 --> 00:56:09,040
Pie, are you almost done?

791
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:10,680
It's almost time for the appointment.

792
00:56:14,200 --> 00:56:17,320
Pun, I've had diarrhea since this morning.

793
00:56:18,760 --> 00:56:19,600
What?

794
00:56:20,320 --> 00:56:21,160
How are you feeling?

795
00:56:22,680 --> 00:56:25,040
What did you eat yesterday? Are you okay?

796
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:27,560
I'm not really sure.

797
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:31,200
I've been going since 4 a.m.
and haven't stopped.

798
00:56:31,720 --> 00:56:33,680
Yesterday, I ate normally.

799
00:56:33,760 --> 00:56:36,320
But I had some spicy food
and a little bit of raw beef salad.

800
00:56:36,920 --> 00:56:38,480
Oh no, Pie.

801
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:40,240
You…

802
00:56:40,320 --> 00:56:42,800
It's all raw food and spicy stuff.

803
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:47,880
Why did you eat that, knowing
you have a doctor's appointment?

804
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:50,280
I'm sorry, Pun.

805
00:56:53,320 --> 00:56:55,840
Pun, I'm sorry, I can't take it anymore.
I'm so sorry.

806
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:04,880
Okay, Pie. I'll cancel the appointment
with Dr. Bee for today.

807
00:57:05,520 --> 00:57:08,360
I'll have Tian bring you
some medicine and breakfast.

808
00:57:16,520 --> 00:57:18,640
My boss is here, over there.

809
00:57:18,720 --> 00:57:20,920
I missed you so much.

810
00:57:24,440 --> 00:57:27,480
I won't lie to Pun anymore.
Whatever happens, happens.

811
00:57:27,560 --> 00:57:30,040
- But…
- Mom, I've made my decision.

812
00:57:30,120 --> 00:57:32,240
I'm ready to face the truth.

813
00:57:32,320 --> 00:57:34,840
If it's not the real deal, not genuine,

814
00:57:34,920 --> 00:57:36,360
it'll eventually fall apart
and deteriorate.

815
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:38,760
<i>Its true nature will be revealed.</i>

816
00:57:38,840 --> 00:57:40,120
What on earth are you doing?

817
00:57:40,200 --> 00:57:42,000
You're really embarrassing.

818
00:57:42,840 --> 00:57:43,680
<i>You can't take it.</i>

819
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:44,880
You don't want to stay.

820
00:57:44,960 --> 00:57:46,280
<i>You want to go home, right?</i>

821
00:57:49,440 --> 00:57:51,640
<i>Maybe they are more suited</i>
<i>to each other than I am.</i>

822
00:57:51,720 --> 00:57:53,840
<i>At this point, if Pun really chooses Mink,</i>

823
00:57:54,600 --> 00:57:55,480
<i>I'll accept it.</i>

824
00:58:20,640 --> 00:58:23,240
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
